1. Consider the following code fragments. For each, if there is a compiler error, identify
where it occurs.
a. First fragment:
List<Integer> ints = new ArrayList<>();
ints.add(1);
ints.add(2);
List<Number> nums = ints; //Compiler error here
nums.add(3.14);
Ans: Java generics are invariant — List<Integer> is not a subtype of List<Number>

b. Second fragment:
List<Integer> ints = new ArrayList<>();
ints.add(1);
ints.add(2);
List<? extends Number> nums = ints;
nums.add(3.14); //Compiler error here
Ans: nums.add(3.14) fails because the compiler cannot verify which specific subtype of Number the list holds at runtime.
